    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-03-24T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-03-24T03:00:00-05:00" n="203"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.11/3–2453: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Saigon</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MR2"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McClintock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-03-24T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 24, 1953—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1840. Dept pass Defense, Pusan. Rptd info Tokyo 53, Paris 259, Pusan 6. Following
                    his interview March 20 with <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName>,
                    General <persName>Clark</persName> said that despite views expressed by
                        <persName corresp="#p_LJ2">Letourneau</persName> (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 1721, March 4, <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss>
                    1812, March 10, Pusan telegram 1106 to Department March 4),<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d203fn1">None printed.</note> he thought considerable benefit might
                    be derived from a visit by <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> to
                    Korea. As <persName>Clark</persName> put it, “We might be able to shame him into
                    being useful.” General added that, if it should be decided to extend <persName
                        corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> an invitation, this should properly come
                    from President Rhee.<note n="2" xml:id="d203fn2">Syngman Rhee, President of the
                        Republic of Korea.</note>
                </p>
                <p>At termination his highly successful four day tour of Indochina, in which he made
                    an outstandingly good impression, General <persName>Clark</persName> announced
                    to press that he had invited Generals <persName corresp="#p_SGR1"
                        >Salan</persName> and <persName>Linares</persName> as well as Vietnamese
                    Chief of Staff General <persName corresp="#p_NVH1">Hinh</persName>, to visit him
                    in Tokyo and to inspect situation in Korea. He will likewise accelerate visit
                    here of training team mission as follow-up to recent Franco–Vietnamese training
                    team visit to Korea.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MR2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">McClintock</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
